The method should return an integer value representing the minimum number of steps required to make `t` an anagram of `s`.
The method should not modify the original strings `s` and `t`.
The method should handle both uppercase and lowercase characters in the strings `s` and `t`.
The method should consider all characters in the strings `s` and `t` for determining the anagram.
The method should return 0 if `s` and `t` are already anagrams of each other.
The method should return -1 if it is not possible to make `t` an anagram of `s` by any number of steps.
